comments: Brogdon (BOS) is moving alongside Porter Jr.'s (HOU) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together at the same spot.
Green (HOU) gathers the ball on his right foot, establishing his left foot as his pivot foot, and he maintains his pivot foot after his gather.
Horford (BOS) cleanly dislodges the ball from Green (HOU) as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Horford (BOS) cleanly ties up Green (HOU) and a jump ball is correctly called.
Porter Jr. (HOU) moves laterally into Brogdon's (BOS) path and initiates contact as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Replay review of the foul called on Tate (HOU) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Tate faces up with Smart (BOS), clamping his arm prior to any contact caused by Smart.
Tate (HOU) establishes himself in Brogdon's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Tate (HOU) establishes himself in Tatum's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Horford (BOS) legally contests Green's (HOU) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Smith Jr. (HOU) extends his hand forward and makes contact with Tatum's (BOS) arm as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Smart (BOS) brings his forearm towards Martin Jr.'s (HOU) slightly extended arm and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the rebound.
Tate (HOU) establishes himself in Smart's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Tatum (BOS) legally contests Smith Jr.'s (HOU) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Tate (HOU) makes contact with Brown's (BOS) arm, which affects his jump shot attempt.
Eason (HOU) and Smart (BOS) come together at the same spot, and incidental leg to leg contact occurs as they position themselves for a potential rebound.
Brown (BOS) brings his hands towards Porter Jr.'s (HOU) side and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Smart (BOS) and Porter Jr. (HOU) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Brown (BOS) makes clean contact with the ball as Porter Jr. (HOU) is passing.  Any ensuing contact after the deflection is considered incidental.
Martin Jr. (HOU) establishes himself in Brogdon's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Brown (BOS) cleanly deflects the ball away from Green (HOU) on the perimeter.
Tatum (BOS) secures possession as he saves the ball and passes it back into play. The shot clock is turned off, and play continues as HOU gains possession of the bad pass.
Tatum (BOS) brings his hand towards Smith Jr.'s (HOU) front and marginal contact occurs as Smith Jr. passes the ball.
Brogdon (BOS) commits a take foul on Green (HOU).
Smart (BOS) commits a take foul on Green (HOU).
Porter Jr. (HOU) is moving alongside Brown's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs as Brown cuts back towards the rim.
White (BOS) commits a take foul on Smith Jr. (HOU).
Smith Jr. (HOU) avoids making contact with Tatum (BOS) as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Eason (HOU) avoids making contact with Tatum (BOS) as he defends the driving shot attempt.
